Members of Congress, including Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and House Majority Leader Kevin McCarthy, are expressing their support for President Trump's infrastructure plan. They believe that rebuilding America's infrastructure is a critical issue and are committed to working together with the President and his administration to achieve this goal. Republicans in Congress are eager to address America's aging infrastructure and outdated rules and regulations that drive up costs. They are calling on Democrats to keep their commitment to achieving these goals and work together in a bipartisan manner. Several senators and representatives are also expressing their support for the President's plan and their willingness to work with the administration to pass a bipartisan infrastructure bill. Cabinet members, including Secretary of the Interior Ryan Zinke and Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue, are also expressing their support for the President's infrastructure agenda. Advocacy organizations, such as the National Association of Manufacturers, are praising the President's call for a substantial investment in infrastructure, noting that it has the potential to boost manufacturing and improve competitiveness.